name: Canary
description: Optimized 2D lattice: qubits and resonators on the same layer.

name: Falcon
description: Flip-chip enabled qubit scaling. Heavy-hex connectivity, optimal for cross-resonance, is pioneered.

name: Hummingbird R2
description: Falcon processor advancements like readout multiplexing and efficient couplers enabled this scalable 65Q Hummingbird design

name: Eagle R3
description: R3 boasts a new architecture with higher qubit coherence, enabling lower gate errors despite longer gate lengths.

name: Heron
description: Featuring a record-low error rate, three times lower than its predecessor from IBM.

name: Willow
description: Error reduction can increase exponentially with the addition of more qubits as scaling up occurs

name: Ocelot
description: A new quantum computing chip that can reduce the costs of implementing quantum error correction. 5 cat qubits (data), 5 stabilization buffers, 4 error-detection qubits.

name: Aquila
description: Vacuum-trapped Rubidium atoms in programmable laser arrays.

name: H1-1
description: Honeywell's next-generation quantum computer, quantum volume 128 with trapped-ion technology

name: H1-2
description: Prove 2,048 Quantum Volume. Powered by Honeywell.

name: H1-1 (upgraded)
description: Up to 20 qubits and a two-qubit gate depth of up to 159. Powered by Honeywell.
